#: ../../SO2.md:233
msgid "2.3. SO 2-3 – Trends in Population Exposure to Land Degradation Disaggregated by Sex"
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:235
msgid "2.3.1. Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:237
msgid "Indicator SO 3-2 was developed in response to decision 11/COP.14 to align the reporting process for SO 1 to 5 with gender-responsive indicators and guidelines and ensure that the gender dimensions of land degradation are captured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:239
msgid "The indicator estimates the proportion of populations exposed to land degradation, disaggregated by sex, as a first step towards addressing the gender data gap on land degradation within the UNCCD reporting framework. The methodology uses the spatial distribution of the population or sub-population group (i.e., by sex) to establish its exposure to land degradation, as determined by indicator SO 1-4 (i.e., SDG Indicator 15.3.1)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:241
msgid "The indicator trends in the proportion of population exposed to land degradation, disaggregated by sex, uses the following metrics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:243
msgid "Percentage of the female population exposed to land degradation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:245
msgid "Percentage of the male population exposed to land degradation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:247
msgid "Percentage of the total (female and male) population exposed to land degradation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:249
msgid "National reporting is facilitated though the provision of default data derived from the Worldpop global dataset on population distributions, demographics and dynamics and the default indicator SO 1-4 estimates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:251
msgid "2.3.2. Prerequisites for reporting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:253
msgid "An in-depth reading of the methodological note for indicator SO 3-2 (see section 2.3.7)."
msgstr ""

