msgid "Population data complying with the specifications listed in table 17."
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:257
msgid "A pool of national experts officially nominated by the national authorities to verify the suitability and consistency of the default data against the situation in their country, or to identify and compile data using national sources for the three metrics. Key institutions might include a country’s national statistical office, ministry of environment and ministry of agriculture, as well as universities and research centres."
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:259
msgid "2.3.3. Reporting process and step-by-step procedure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:261
msgid "The step-by-step procedure for reporting is described in the following. If Parties decide to use the default data, steps 2 and 3 are unnecessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:263
msgid "Step 1: Select the population dataset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:265
msgid "Suitable data for the calculation of indicator SO 2-3 is a sex-disaggregated gridded count of the human population, or a georeferenced set of sub-national data that covers the full extent of the country. It must represent the number of male and female individuals per grid cell, ideally annually, in the time period in question (i.e., the date timestamp should be at least one of the years within the baseline and reporting period)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:267
msgid "Among the publicly available population datasets at the global scale, the WorldPop dataset is used by default by the UNCCD for calculating indicator SO2-3 and provided to Parties in Trends.Earth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:269
msgid "An alternative dataset is the Gridded Population of the World, version 4 (GPWv4)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../SO2.md:271
msgid "Parties may also use national data, provided it complies with the data specifications listed in table 17."
msgstr ""

